    <title>Changing the MTU on a small-footprint System using the CLI</title>
    <shortdesc>
        <draft-comment author="rstone">Topic created for CGTS-1944</draft-comment>
    </shortdesc>
    <prolog><author/>
        <author>Ron Stone</author>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <context id="context_N10026_N10023_N10001">
            <p>The following steps illustrate how to change the MTU for an interface
                for an infrastructure network. This example uses eth6 as the interface to be
                changed.</p>
        </context>
        <steps>
            <step id="step_N10036_N10033_N10023_N10001">
                <cmd>Lock controller-1.</cmd>
                <stepxmp>
                    <codeblock><systemoutput>~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput>system host-lock controller-1</userinput></codeblock>
                </stepxmp>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N1004C_N10033_N10023_N10001">
                <cmd>Modify the MTU of an interface on controller-1.</cmd>
                <stepxmp>
                    <codeblock><systemoutput>~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput>system host-if-modify controller-1 eth6 --imtu 1600</userinput></codeblock>
                </stepxmp>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N10063_N10033_N10023_N10001">
                <cmd>Unlock controller-1.</cmd>
                <stepxmp>
                    <codeblock><systemoutput>~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput>system host-unlock controller-1</userinput></codeblock>
                </stepxmp>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N10079_N10033_N10023_N10001">
                <cmd>Swact the host to controller-1. </cmd>
                <stepxmp>
                    <codeblock><systemoutput>~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput>system host-swact controller-1</userinput></codeblock>
                </stepxmp>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N1008F_N10033_N10023_N10001">
                <cmd>Lock controller-0.</cmd>
                <stepxmp>
                    <codeblock><systemoutput>~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput>system host-lock controller-0</userinput></codeblock>
                </stepxmp>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N100A5_N10033_N10023_N10001">
                <cmd>Modify the MTU of the interface on controller-0. </cmd>
                <stepxmp>
                    <codeblock><systemoutput>~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput>system host-if-modify controller-0 eth6 --imtu 1600</userinput></codeblock>
                </stepxmp>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N100BC_N10033_N10023_N10001">
                <cmd>Unlock controller-0. </cmd>
                <stepxmp>
                    <codeblock><systemoutput>~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput>system host-unlock controller-0</userinput></codeblock>
                </stepxmp>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task-wr>
